/*	Zinc JS: a small JavaScript interpreter. Public Domain.

	Enough of the language to run simple page scripts:
	  var/let/const, function decls and expressions, if/else, while, for,
	  return, break, ?:, && ||, arithmetic and comparisons, strings with
	  methods (length, charAt, indexOf, substring, slice, toUpperCase,
	  toLowerCase), arrays (literals, indexing, length, push, join, indexOf),
	  object literals.
	DOM bindings:
	  document.write, document.title, document.getElementById, element
	  innerHTML/textContent/value/checked/className/style.X, get/setAttribute,
	  location.href (assignment navigates), alert, console.log, Math.*,
	  parseInt, parseFloat, String, Number, isNaN, Date.now.
	Async + events (need the front-end to call JsEventLoopPump / JsDispatchEvent):
	  setTimeout/setInterval/clearTimeout/clearInterval (real, deferred),
	  addEventListener/removeEventListener, el.onclick = function, and
	  XMLHttpRequest (open/send/responseText/status/onload/onreadystatechange;
	  the fetch is synchronous under the hood, callbacks fire on the next pump).
	Language v2 (Phase B): closures (functions capture their defining env),
	arrow functions, template literals (lexer-desugared to concatenation),
	for-of / for-in, try/catch/finally + throw, class declarations
	(constructor + methods via a real prototype chain), new-expressions with
	prototype linking, this binding, numeric/method object-literal keys.
	Not supported (script just errors out harmlessly): regex literals,
	do/switch, destructuring, spread, getters/setters, async/await,
	fetch()/Promise (queued for Phase B part 2), bitwise ops.

	All interpreter memory comes from a per-page arena freed in one shot by
	JsInterpFree. Execution has step and call-depth budgets, so hostile or
	looping scripts cannot hang the browser.

	Needs: HTML.ZC. No literal dollar signs allowed in this file. */

#define JS_MAX_SRC			2097152	// = HTTP_BODY_MAX: bigger can't arrive anyway
#define JS_MAX_STEPS		2000000
#define JS_MAX_DEPTH		48
#define JS_MAX_ARGS			8
#define JS_WRITE_BUF		131072

